gomodel:SYNGO_2565  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Results section. \"Ultrastructural localization of Syt11 in rat hippocampal CA1 synapses by immunoelectron microscopy\"\n\n-Literal: \" We finally examined the ultrastructural distribution of Syt11 protein in rat hippocampus by immunogold EM (Fig. 6) ...In axon terminals, Syt11 signals were colocalized with presynaptic vesicles...\"\n\n22/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Methods section: \"Electron microcopy\"\n\n-Literal. \"Ultrastructural subcellular localization of Syt11 in rat brains was examined using immuno-EM, as described previously (Paik et al., 2011). CA1 hippocampal sections of rat brains (60 lm; 8 weeks) were incubated for 2 h with goat anti-Syt11 antibodies (1:200) and rabbit anti-goat IgG 10 nm gold-conjugated (EMS, #25228, SUA) .....\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2565" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

